Cape Flats residents held a memorial service on Wednesday for Noluvo Swelindawo who was murdered allegedly because of her lesbian lifestyle.Swelindawo was allegedly abducted and assaulted by ten men who broke into her home on Saturday night.Her body was discovered with a gunshot wound near the N2 highway.Last week Wednesday a man appeared at the Blue Downs Magistrate Court in connection with the murder of Noluvo Swelindawo in Driftsands.The 24-year-old suspect appeared in court on charges of murder and kidnapping.Police spokesperson FC Van Wyk said the investigation into the murder led to the arrest of the suspect. Our investigation into the murder of Noluvo led to the arrest of the suspect on Monday afternoon , Van Wyk said.-TNA Reporter 